.TH hsh 1 "December 2025" "Holberton School" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
hsh \- simple UNIX command interpreter
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hsh
[file]
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.B hsh
program is a simple UNIX command interpreter developed as part of the Holberton School curriculum.
It reads commands from standard input in interactive mode or from a file in non-interactive mode,
and executes them in the same way as
.B /bin/sh .
.SH BUILTINS
The following built-in commands are supported:
.TP
.B exit
Exit the shell. An optional status argument may be provided.
.TP
.B env
Print the current environment variables.
.SH USAGE
Interactive mode:
.PP
.RS
$ ./hsh
($) /bin/ls
($) exit
.RE
.PP
Non-interactive mode:
.PP
.RS
$ echo "/bin/ls" | ./hsh
.RE
.SH EXIT STATUS
The shell returns 0 on success.
If a command is not found, it returns 127.
If a command exists but cannot be executed, it returns 126.
.SH DIAGNOSTICS
Error messages follow the format:
.PP
.RS
<program_name>: <command_number>: <command>: not found
.RE
.SH ENVIRONMENT
The shell uses the
.B PATH
environment variable to locate executables.
It inherits the environment from its parent process.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR sh (1),
.BR execve (2)
.SH AUTHORS
